message.content:
A toaster is a small household appliance used to toast slices of bread. 
It typically has a rectangular shape with slots for bread on top. 
It often features a lever to lower the bread into the slots and a dial to adjust the toasting time. 
The exterior is usually made of metal, plastic, or a combination of both. 
The interior contains heating elements that radiate heat to toast the bread. 
Toasters can be found in kitchens, restaurants, cafeterias, and other food-related settings. 
They are a staple appliance for breakfast and snack time.
